Company Description: Established in 1926, Pacific Clinics was previously known as Pasadena Child Guidance Clinic. Located in Pomona, Calif., it is a non-profit community behavioral healthcare agency. The company offers a range of services for substance abuse, families, children, teens, transitional age youth, adults, older adults, as well as housing and multicultural services. Pacific Clinics addresses the mental and behavioral health concerns of families and individuals of all ages. Moreover, it has a Pacific Clinics Training Institute (PCTI) offering a variety of educational opportunities.
